WARRI – All standing revenue committees in Udu Local Government Area of Delta State have been dissolved The dissolution was contained in a public announcement signed and released by Secretary to Udu local government area, Comrade Sam Dawho on Friday on behalf of the council Boss, Chief Onajite Brown. The statement added that only the transport Sub-Committee headed by Chief Obruche Oghenejiru and Sub- Committee on Tenement rate on privately owned houses headed by Evangelist( Hon) Lucky Esedafetoma were exempted from the dissolution of committees. Lukaku Apologises For Interview Discussing Inter Akume’s Birthday: APC Officials At Daggers Drawn Over… The Chairman of Udu Local Government Council Hon. Chief Jite Brown (JP) in the statement, directed all Chairmen of various committees to hand over all Council properties in their possession to the office of the Secretary to Udu Local Government Council within 24 hours of this announcement, adding that the Udu Local Government Council will in due course reconstitute new revenue sub- Committees for the year 2022 and announce same to the general public. According to the statement, all revenues due to the Local Government Council shall be paid directly to the Udu Local Government Council Account domiciled at Union Bank( Udu Road Branch). According to the statement, “the general public is hereby informed that security agencies have been notified to deal with anyone or persons who disobeys this order. “The Local Government Council Chairman sincerely appreciates all members of the various Committees for their individual and collective contributions towards the development of the Local Government and wish them well in their future endeavours”, the statement added.